{"header":"<h1>Module <code><span>Data.Range_tree</span></code></h1>","type":"documentation","uses_katex":false,"breadcrumbs":[{"name":"Index","href":"../../../../index.html","kind":"leaf-page"},{"name":"soteria","href":"../../../index.html","kind":"page"},{"name":"Soteria","href":"../../index.html","kind":"module"},{"name":"Data","href":"../index.html","kind":"module"},{"name":"Range_tree","href":"#","kind":"module"}],"toc":[],"source_anchor":null,"preamble":"<p>This module describe &quot;Range trees&quot;, a datastructure for symbolic reasoning about a range of data.</p><p>Range trees are representation of an array of symbolic size. Each node of the tree represents a contiguous range of the array (a <a href=\"../S_range/Make/index.html#type-t\"><code>S_range.Make.t</code></a> using a given type of symbolic integers <code>'sint</code>). Each node also some data, which must be mergeable.</p><p>Each node has either no children, or exactly two children, which represent a split of the node's range into two contiguous subranges, i.e. if the parent node covers <code>a..c</code> (note that it doesn't include &quot;c&quot;), then the children must cover <code>a..b</code> and <code>b..c</code> with <code>a &lt; b &lt; c</code>.</p><p>Additionally, we maintain the invariant that the tree is balanced, i.e. for any node, the height of its left and right children can differ by at most 1. This is for obvious performance reasons.</p>","content":"<div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec type anchored\" id=\"type-info\"><a href=\"#type-info\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">type</span> info</span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Type describing the information associated to a range tree, such as its height and whether it is balanced. Opaque because it is optimised.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec type anchored\" id=\"type-t\"><a href=\"#type-t\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">type</span> <span>('a, 'sint) t</span></span><span> = <span class=\"keyword\">private</span> </span><span>{</span></code><ol><li id=\"type-t.node\" class=\"def record field anchored\"><a href=\"#type-t.node\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span>node : <span class=\"type-var\">'a</span>;</span></code></li><li id=\"type-t.range\" class=\"def record field anchored\"><a href=\"#type-t.range\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span>range : <span class=\"type-var\">'sint</span> * <span class=\"type-var\">'sint</span>;</span></code></li><li id=\"type-t.children\" class=\"def record field anchored\"><a href=\"#type-t.children\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span>children : <span><span>(<span><span>(<span class=\"type-var\">'a</span>, <span class=\"type-var\">'sint</span>)</span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span> * <span><span>(<span class=\"type-var\">'a</span>, <span class=\"type-var\">'sint</span>)</span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span>)</span> option</span>;</span></code></li><li id=\"type-t.info\" class=\"def record field anchored\"><a href=\"#type-t.info\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span>info : <a href=\"#type-info\">info</a>;</span></code></li></ol><code><span>}</span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>A &quot;Range Tree&quot;, representing a symbolic range of data sequences <code>'a</code>, using ranges over symbolic integer representation <code>'sint</code>.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-pp\"><a href=\"#val-pp\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> pp : <span><span><span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <span class=\"xref-unresolved\">Fmt</span>.t</span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span><span class=\"type-var\">'sint</span> <span class=\"xref-unresolved\">Fmt</span>.t</span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span><span>(<span class=\"type-var\">'a</span>, <span class=\"type-var\">'sint</span>)</span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span> <span class=\"xref-unresolved\">Fmt</span>.t</span></span></code></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-height\"><a href=\"#val-height\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> height : <span><span><span>(<span class=\"type-var\">'a</span>, <span class=\"type-var\">'sint</span>)</span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> int</span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Maximum depth of the tree.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-is_balanced\"><a href=\"#val-is_balanced\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> is_balanced : <span><span><span>(<span class=\"type-var\">'a</span>, <span class=\"type-var\">'sint</span>)</span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> bool</span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Whether <em>all</em> nodes of the tree are balanced.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-make_raw\"><a href=\"#val-make_raw\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> make_raw : \u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">node</span>:<span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">range</span>:<span>(<span class=\"type-var\">'sint</span> * <span class=\"type-var\">'sint</span>)</span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span class=\"optlabel\">?children</span>:<span>(<span><span>(<span class=\"type-var\">'a</span>, <span class=\"type-var\">'sint</span>)</span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span> * <span><span>(<span class=\"type-var\">'a</span>, <span class=\"type-var\">'sint</span>)</span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span>)</span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span>unit <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span>(<span class=\"type-var\">'a</span>, <span class=\"type-var\">'sint</span>)</span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Creates a tree node without ensuring that it is balanced.</p></div></div><p>Creates a tree with no children (and therefore does not) need to be balanced.</p><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-build_leaf\"><a href=\"#val-build_leaf\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> build_leaf : <span><span class=\"label\">node</span>:<span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span class=\"label\">range</span>:<span>(<span class=\"type-var\">'sint</span> * <span class=\"type-var\">'sint</span>)</span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span>unit <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span>(<span class=\"type-var\">'a</span>, <span class=\"type-var\">'sint</span>)</span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span></span></code></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-build\"><a href=\"#val-build\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> build : \u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">node</span>:<span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">range</span>:<span>(<span class=\"type-var\">'sint</span> * <span class=\"type-var\">'sint</span>)</span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">merge</span>:<span>(<span><span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span class=\"type-var\">'a</span>)</span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span class=\"optlabel\">?children</span>:<span>(<span><span>(<span class=\"type-var\">'a</span>, <span class=\"type-var\">'sint</span>)</span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span> * <span><span>(<span class=\"type-var\">'a</span>, <span class=\"type-var\">'sint</span>)</span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span>)</span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span>unit <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span>(<span class=\"type-var\">'a</span>, <span class=\"type-var\">'sint</span>)</span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Builds a tree given a node, a range, and children, and automatically balances it.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-rebuild\"><a href=\"#val-rebuild\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> rebuild : <span><span class=\"label\">merge</span>:<span>(<span><span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span class=\"type-var\">'a</span>)</span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span><span>(<span class=\"type-var\">'a</span>, <span class=\"type-var\">'sint</span>)</span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span>(<span class=\"type-var\">'a</span>, <span class=\"type-var\">'sint</span>)</span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Rebalances an existing tree bottom-up, using <code>merge</code> to recompute intermediate node values created during rotations.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-offset\"><a href=\"#val-offset\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> offset : \u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">add</span>:<span>(<span><span class=\"type-var\">'sint</span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span class=\"type-var\">'sint</span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span class=\"type-var\">'sint</span>)</span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">by</span>:<span class=\"type-var\">'sint</span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span><span>(<span class=\"type-var\">'a</span>, <span class=\"type-var\">'sint</span>)</span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span>(<span class=\"type-var\">'a</span>, <span class=\"type-var\">'sint</span>)</span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p><code>offset ~apply_ofs t</code> uses the function <code>apply_ofs</code> on all offset in the ranges of the tree <code>t</code>.</p><p>Effectively, this function is just a <code>map_offsets</code>, but applying any other transformation to the offsets of the tree than offsetting by a constant integer is invalid.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-iter_leaves_rev\"><a href=\"#val-iter_leaves_rev\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> iter_leaves_rev : <span><span><span>(<span class=\"type-var\">'a</span>, <span class=\"type-var\">'sint</span>)</span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span>(<span><span><span>(<span class=\"type-var\">'a</span>, <span class=\"type-var\">'sint</span>)</span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> unit)</span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> unit</span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p><code>iter_leaves_rev t</code> is an iterator over the leaves of the tree <code>t</code> from right to left.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-map_leaves\"><a href=\"#val-map_leaves\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> map_leaves : \u000A  <span>(<span class=\"keyword\">module</span> M : <a href=\"../../Soteria_std/Compo_res/module-type-Base/index.html\">Soteria.Soteria_std.Compo_res.Base</a>)</span>\u000A  <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span>\u000A  <span><span>(<span><span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span>(<span class=\"type-var\">'a</span>, <span class=\"type-var\">'b</span>, <span class=\"type-var\">'c</span>)</span> <span class=\"xref-unresolved\">M.t</span></span>)</span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span><span>(<span class=\"type-var\">'a</span>, <span class=\"type-var\">'sint</span>)</span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span>(<span><span>(<span class=\"type-var\">'a</span>, <span class=\"type-var\">'sint</span>)</span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span>, <span class=\"type-var\">'b</span>, <span class=\"type-var\">'c</span>)</span> <span class=\"xref-unresolved\">M.t</span></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p><code>map_leaves M f t</code> receives a mapping function <code>f</code> operating within the monad <code>M</code>, as well as a tree, and applys <code>f</code> to all <b>leaves</b> of the tree (not the inner nodes).</p></div></div>"}